<span style="font-family:georgia; font-size: 20px">
The BRICK Ministries, Inc. is recognized as a non-profit organization with tax-exempt status under section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code.  Your gift is tax deductible.

With your donation, you will help to support program participants receive food, and assistance with emergency financial needs.

You can mail donations to <strong>The BRICK</strong> at:
420 Ellis Ave.
Ashland, WI 54806

For an online donation, please use the <strong>PayPal</strong> link at the bottom of this page. You can also drop off donations at any of our 4 food shelf locations.

<img src="http://thebrickministries.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/Golf-Check-2013.png" alt="Golf Check 2013" style="width: 75%; height: 50%; border: 2px solid #000000">

There are several opportunities for you to direct your financial donation. If you would like your donation to go to a specific fund, please write the fund on the memo line of your check, or make a note within the PayPal submission. If you do not designate where to apply your donation, we will simply use your donation where it is most needed.

<strong>Make A Difference Fund
</strong>The Make A Difference Fund provides assistance for families in crisis and facing difficulties paying for utilities, rent, and other basic needs.
Your financial gift is <em>matched dollar for dollar</em> up to $25,000, thanks to donations made from Northern State Bank, Bretting Manufacturing, Deltco Plastics and Recycling, and Memorial Medical Center.
Contributions go directly to The BRICK’s Benevolence account for emergency help.

<img src="http://thebrickministries.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/Jim-Coolers.jpg" alt="Jim &amp; Coolers"  style="width: 75%; height: 50%; border: 2px solid #000000" >

<strong>Food Shelf Funds
</strong>Your donation to the food shelf will aid in purchasing food for community distribution in all of our food shelves located in Ashland, Mellen, Cornucopia, and Cable.

<strong>The BRICK's General Operating Fund
</strong>The general operating fund helps us to keep our lights on, the copier running, and all the general operating expenses that go along with helping our community.

